<title>HONG KONG: HK's Hutchison, Cheung Kong to set US$100 mln loan.</title>
<headline>HK's Hutchison, Cheung Kong to set US$100 mln loan.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-02-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Hutchison Whampoa and Cheung Kong Holdings have mandated Sumitomo Bank Hong Kong and Chase Manhattan Asia to arrange a US$100 million loan facility, bankers said.</p>
<p>The deal is fully guaranteed by the two Hong Kong conglomerates, bankers said.</p>
<p>The facility has a final maturity of seven years with a put option in year five.</p>
<p>Proceeds are to be used for financing a property development in Shanghai.</p>
<p>--Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2847 4039</p>
